puzzle.help: 1. Each Magnet has a positive(+) and a negative(-) pole. 2. Every rectangle can either contain a Magnet or be empty. 3. The number on the board tells you how many positive and negative poles you can see from there in a straight line. 4. When placing a Magnet, you have to respect the rule that the same pole (+ and + / - and -) can't be adjacent horizontally or vertically. 5. In some levels, a few numbers on the border can be hidden.
